Whisk together egg whites, egg, and pepper in small bowl. Set aside. Heat oil in wok or large nonstick skillet over high heat. Add asparagus, scallions, edamame, garlic, and ginger. Stir-fry 6 minutes. Add egg mixture and soy sauce. Stir-fry until egg is just cooked through, about 30 seconds. Toss with cilantro.